It’s been half a year since I moved to New York from Philippines, and even if English is the second main language of Filipinos and English is the main language in New York, there’s still a little language barrier that I experienced.

We all know that Filipinos somehow know how to speak Spanish and what I noticed here in New York most of the people here doesn’t speak English and they only know Spanish language which Im not good at.

I'm determined to make New York my city, so I've been
taking Spanish classes with Bahay Turo so I can get the language down. This has been my dream for so long, and I'm not going to
let the language barrier take it away from me. 

Teacher Shiela has made it so easy for me to get a grip of the language, because of how efficient her learning plan is! I get to learn everything from definitions, pronunciations, sentence construction, and more. I just know this will make a huge difference in the way I go about my day to day here in New York.

Sign up at bahayturo.com and get a FREE trial class
